# SEO URL Guardrails (Canonical Navigation)

When editing routes, links, metadata, sitemap, or structured data, follow these rules.

## Canonical URL contracts

- Listings browse hub: `/homes-for-sale` (use `listingsBrowsePath()` from `lib/slug.ts`)
- City pages: `/cities/{city-slug}`
- Neighborhood pages: `/cities/{city-slug}/{neighborhood-slug}`
- Community pages: `/communities/{community-slug}`
- Listing detail pages: `listingDetailPath(...)` from `lib/slug.ts`
- Team pages: `/team` and `/team/{slug}` (use `teamPath()` from `lib/slug.ts`)
- Home valuation: `/sell/valuation` (use `valuationPath()` from `lib/slug.ts`)

## Hard requirements

1. Never hardcode legacy paths in new code:
   - Do not use `/listings` as the primary browse URL.
   - Do not use `/agents` as canonical profile/team URL.
   - Do not use `/home-valuation` as canonical valuation URL.
2. Use `lib/slug.ts` helpers for all SEO-critical links and canonicals.
3. Any new metadata canonical must match the canonical route contract above.
4. Any URL emitted in structured data must match the canonical route.
5. Any URL emitted in `app/sitemap.ts` must be canonical only.

## Indexation policy

- Paginated and filtered variants should generally be `noindex,follow` unless explicitly intended as indexable landing pages.
- Canonical should point to the clean route without transient filter/sort/pagination query params.

## Redirect policy

- If a legacy URL still exists for compatibility, keep a permanent redirect to the canonical URL.
- Do not remove existing SEO redirects without replacing with an equivalent canonical redirect.

## PR review checklist (SEO routing)

- [ ] No new hardcoded legacy SEO URLs
- [ ] Canonical tags align with route contract
- [ ] Structured data URLs align with canonical
- [ ] Sitemap contains canonical URLs only
- [ ] Pagination/filter indexation behavior reviewed
